---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Participant Handbook - Explore China"
  description="Read the Explore China participant handbook for travel preparation, accommodation, payment setup, and arrival guidance."
  lang="en"
  alternateHref="/zh/handbook"
  alternateLabel="中文"
  canonical="/handbook"
  darkNav={true}
>

  <div class="handbook-page">

    <!-- 1. Page Header -->
    <header class="handbook-header">
      <p class="handbook-header__eyebrow">Explore China 2026</p>
      <h1 class="handbook-header__title">Participant Handbook</h1>
      <p class="handbook-header__sub">This handbook is for confirmed participants. Everything you need to know before departure — visa, apps, payments, SIM cards, and more.</p>
    </header>

    <!-- Section Nav -->
    <nav class="handbook-nav" aria-label="Handbook sections">
      <p class="handbook-nav__label">Jump to section</p>
      <ul class="handbook-nav__list">
        <li><a href="#checklist">Quick Pre-Departure Checklist</a></li>
        <li><a href="#visa">Passport &amp; Entry</a></li>
        <li><a href="#vpn">VPN Setup</a></li>
        <li><a href="#sim">SIM / Internet</a></li>
        <li><a href="#apps">Apps &amp; Payment Setup</a></li>
        <li><a href="#packing" class="stub-link">Packing &amp; Gear</a></li>
        <li><a href="#arrival" class="stub-link">Flight &amp; Arrival</a></li>
        <li><a href="#transport" class="stub-link">In-China Transport</a></li>
        <li><a href="#health" class="stub-link">Health &amp; Insurance</a></li>
        <li><a href="#emergency" class="stub-link">Emergency Contacts</a></li>
        <li><a href="#schedule" class="stub-link">Program Schedule</a></li>
      </ul>
    </nav>

    <!-- 2. Quick Checklist -->
    <section id="checklist" class="handbook-section">
      <p class="section-sub-label">Before you leave</p>
      <h2>Quick Pre-Departure Checklist</h2>
      <ul class="handbook-checklist">
        <li>
          <span class="check-box" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          <span>Check visa eligibility for your passport</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="check-box" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          <span>Install and test VPN before entering China</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="check-box" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          <span>Download WeChat and Alipay — link your Visa/Mastercard</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="check-box" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          <span>Decide on SIM card option</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="check-box" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          <span>Download DiDi (transport app)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="check-warning">
          <span class="check-box" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          <span>⚠ Do NOT set up payment apps while VPN is on</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- 3. Passport & Entry -->
    <section id="visa" class="handbook-section">
      <p class="section-sub-label">Entry requirements</p>
      <h2>Passport &amp; Entry (Canada)</h2>
      <p>Canadian passport holders can enter China <strong>visa-free for up to 30 days</strong>. This policy is valid until the end of 2026. Many other passport holders qualify for a <strong>10-day (240-hour) visa-free transit</strong> — check your specific passport carefully.</p>

      <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;"><strong>Current entry strategy:</strong> Canada passport holders can enter on a visa-free basis (essentially visa-on-arrival). You will need to have the following ready before arriving:</p>

      <ol class="handbook-steps" style="margin-top:0.5rem;">
        <li>Hotel booking confirmation for your stay</li>
        <li>Return/onward flight ticket booked before arrival</li>
        <li>Passport valid for at least 6 months beyond your travel dates</li>
      </ol>

      <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;">Always verify your eligibility before booking flights, as policies can change without notice.</p>

      <div class="handbook-warning">
        <p>⚠ Visa policies can change. Verify eligibility at official sources below before your trip.</p>
        <p>⚠ You must have a confirmed hotel booking and departure flight before arrival.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="handbook-links">
        <a class="handbook-link" href="https://ca.china-embassy.gov.cn" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Chinese Embassy in Canada → ca.china-embassy.gov.cn</a>
        <a class="handbook-link" href="https://toronto.china-consulate.gov.cn" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Chinese Consulate in Toronto → toronto.china-consulate.gov.cn</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 4. VPN Setup -->
    <section id="vpn" class="handbook-section">
      <p class="section-sub-label">Internet access</p>
      <h2>Install your VPN before you land — it cannot be downloaded inside China</h2>
      <p>Google, Instagram, WhatsApp, and YouTube are blocked in China. You must install and test your VPN <strong>before boarding your flight</strong>. Once inside China, the App Store and VPN websites are inaccessible.</p>

      <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;"><strong>Recommended VPN providers:</strong></p>
      <div class="handbook-vpn-list">
        <span class="handbook-vpn-badge">ExpressVPN</span>
        <span class="handbook-vpn-badge">NordVPN</span>
        <span class="handbook-vpn-badge">Astrill</span>
      </div>

      <div class="handbook-warning" style="margin-top:1.25rem;">
        <p>⚠ Install and test your VPN before entering China.</p>
        <p>⚠ Do NOT use VPN when setting up Alipay or WeChat Pay — verification will fail.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 5. SIM / Internet -->
    <section id="sim" class="handbook-section">
      <p class="section-sub-label">Connectivity</p>
      <h2>SIM / Internet</h2>
      <p>A reliable data connection is essential — apps like WeChat Pay and DiDi require it to function. Consider your options before departure.</p>

      <div class="handbook-sim-cards">
        <div class="handbook-sim-card">
          <span class="badge-recommended">Recommended</span>
          <div class="handbook-sim-card__name">International Traveller SIM</div>
          <div class="handbook-sim-card__desc">Available for pickup at the airport. Ask your provider specifically about Google and WhatsApp access.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="handbook-sim-card">
          <div class="handbook-sim-card__name">eSIM</div>
          <div class="handbook-sim-card__desc">Set up before you depart. Convenient, but you won't have a Chinese phone number for SMS verification.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="handbook-sim-card">
          <div class="handbook-sim-card__name">Local Chinese SIM</div>
          <div class="handbook-sim-card__desc">Most stable for app verification and ride-hailing. Requires VPN for accessing Google and Western apps.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="handbook-aside">
        <p><strong>Community tip:</strong> Local SIM is usually more reliable for ride-hailing and app verification — but you'll need your VPN set up (and off) at the right times.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 6. Apps & Payment Setup -->
    <section id="apps" class="handbook-section">
      <p class="section-sub-label">Essential apps</p>
      <h2>Apps &amp; Payment Setup</h2>
      <p>These three apps are essential for daily life in China. Download and set them up before you land.</p>

      <div class="handbook-app-cards">
        <div class="handbook-app-card">
          <div class="handbook-app-card__icon">💬</div>
          <div class="handbook-app-card__name">WeChat</div>
          <div class="handbook-app-card__desc">Chat + payment in one. Primary channel for group communication during the program.</div>
          <div class="handbook-app-card__setup">
            <p class="setup-label">Payment setup:</p>
            <ol>
              <li>Register with your phone number</li>
              <li>Verify identity with passport</li>
              <li>Link Visa/Mastercard</li>
            </ol>
            <a class="handbook-link" href="https://www.wechat.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">WeChat → wechat.com</a>
            <a class="handbook-link" href="https://pay.weixin.qq.com/index.php/public/wechatpay_en" target="_blank" rel="noopener">WeChat Pay setup →</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="handbook-app-card">
          <div class="handbook-app-card__icon">💳</div>
          <div class="handbook-app-card__name">Alipay</div>
          <div class="handbook-app-card__desc">Main payment method accepted at most shops and restaurants across China.</div>
          <div class="handbook-app-card__setup">
            <p class="setup-label">Payment setup:</p>
            <ol>
              <li>Register with your phone number</li>
              <li>Verify identity with passport</li>
              <li>Link Visa/Mastercard</li>
            </ol>
            <a class="handbook-link" href="https://www.alipay.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Alipay → alipay.com</a>
            <a class="handbook-link" href="https://global.alipay.com/docs/ac/setup" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Alipay setup guide (international) →</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="handbook-app-card">
          <div class="handbook-app-card__icon">🚗</div>
          <div class="handbook-app-card__name">DiDi</div>
          <div class="handbook-app-card__desc">Ride-hailing app (like Uber). Works best with a local SIM card for SMS verification.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="handbook-warning">
        <p>⚠ Set up payment apps before arriving in China. Do NOT use VPN during setup — verification will fail.</p>
      </div>
      <p class="handbook-note">These apps work for most shops, restaurants, and transit. P2P transfers may be restricted for foreign cards. Bring some cash (RMB) as a backup.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- 7. Packing & Gear (stub) -->
    <section id="packing" class="handbook-section handbook-section--stub">
      <h2>Packing &amp; Gear</h2>
      <div class="stub-box">
        <span class="stub-icon">🔜</span>
        <p>This section is being prepared. Check back closer to departure.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 8. Flight & Arrival (stub) -->
    <section id="arrival" class="handbook-section handbook-section--stub">
      <h2>Flight &amp; Arrival</h2>
      <div class="stub-box">
        <span class="stub-icon">🔜</span>
        <p>This section is being prepared. Check back closer to departure.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 9. In-China Transport (stub) -->
    <section id="transport" class="handbook-section handbook-section--stub">
      <h2>In-China Transport</h2>
      <div class="stub-box">
        <span class="stub-icon">🔜</span>
        <p>This section is being prepared. Check back closer to departure.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 10. Health & Insurance (stub) -->
    <section id="health" class="handbook-section handbook-section--stub">
      <h2>Health &amp; Insurance</h2>
      <div class="stub-box">
        <span class="stub-icon">🔜</span>
        <p>This section is being prepared. Check back closer to departure.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 11. Emergency Contacts (stub) -->
    <section id="emergency" class="handbook-section handbook-section--stub">
      <h2>Emergency Contacts</h2>
      <div class="stub-box">
        <span class="stub-icon">🔜</span>
        <p>This section is being prepared. Check back closer to departure.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 12. Program Schedule (stub) -->
    <section id="schedule" class="handbook-section handbook-section--stub">
      <h2>Program Schedule</h2>
      <div class="stub-box">
        <span class="stub-icon">🔜</span>
        <p>This section is being prepared. Check back closer to departure.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

  </div>

</Layout>

<style>
  .handbook-app-card__setup {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    padding-top: 1rem;
    border-top: 1px solid #e7e5e4;
  }
  .handbook-app-card__setup .setup-label {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #78716c;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }
  .handbook-app-card__setup ol {
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: #57534e;
  }
  .handbook-app-card__setup ol li {
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }
  .handbook-app-card__setup .handbook-link {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }
</style>
